In this letter, President Barack Obama announces his decision to activate members of the Selected Reserve and certain members of the Individual Ready Reserve to support Operation United Assistance. This operation aims to provide humanitarian assistance and manage the consequences of the Ebola virus disease outbreak in West Africa. The President authorizes the Secretaries of Defense and Homeland Security to order these reservists to active duty in order to augment the active forces in this effort. The President states that invoking these authorities will ensure that the Department of Defense can adequately sustain the military operations required for this mission.